<TITLE> Suspected extremist killed in Jhenaidah </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jhenaidah, Nov 8 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected extremist leader was killed in a gunfight with police in Jhenaidah early on Sunday. Police identified the man as Smarjit Ghosh, 45, a central leader of Bangladesh Biplabi Communist Party. Jhenaidah police super Md Rezaul Karim said they got a tip off that a group of extremists were holding a secret meeting at Depholbaria village under sadar Upazila and raided the spot at around 2am. Sensing presence of the law enforcers, the suspects opened fire at the police forcing them to retaliate in self-defence, he said. During the shootout, which lasted about 20 minutes, the other suspects fled the scene. Police recovered Smarjit's body and one light gun, four rounds of ammunition and two hand made bombs from the spot, Karim said. Smarjit faced several cases including murder cases, the police super said. bdn
